The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, May 25, 2004 				 Jessop Q4 net at Rs 1.43 cr
																								Calcutta, May 24 (PTI): Jessop amp; Co Ltd has posted a net profit of Rs 1.43 crore in the fourth quarter of 2003-04, while it had been able to reduce losses substantially from Rs 50.09 crore in 2002-03 to Rs 6.38 crore in the last financial year.																								Net sales of the firm, which is now under the management control of the Ruia group, increased 23 per cent to Rs 46.35 crore compared with Rs 37.71 crore in 2002-03. Other income of the company registered a fall from Rs 13.70 crore in 2002-03 to Rs 5.80 crore in 2003-04.																								Post-divestment, the government still holds 27 per cent share in the company, while 72 per cent was sold to the Ruia group.																								Jessop chairman P. K. Ruia said a reversal in the fortunes of the company was made possible by a combined effort of the workers and management.																								He said the order book position of the company was good at the moment.
